lead_paragraph: Ivan Dominguez, a Cuban riding for Toyota-United, won the 71.8-mile opening stage of the weeklong Tour de Georgia, sprinting across the finish line a tenth of a second ahead of a crowded peloton. Dominguez finished the stage from Tybee Island to Savannah in 2 hours 30 minutes 18 seconds.
